<item>
            <title>[SPARK-26068] ChunkedByteBufferInputStream is truncated by empty chunk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-26068</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If&#160;ChunkedByteBuffer&#160;contains empty chunk in the middle of it, then the&#160;ChunkedByteBufferInputStream will be&#160;truncated. All data behind the empty chunk will not be read.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The&#160;problematic code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ChunkedByteBuffer.scala
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Assume chunks.next returns an empty chunk, then we will reach
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; branch no matter chunks.hasNext = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; or not. So some data is lost.
&lt;/span&gt;override def read(dest: Array[&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Byte&lt;/span&gt;], offset: Int, length: Int): Int = {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (currentChunk != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !currentChunk.hasRemaining &amp;amp;&amp;amp; chunks.hasNext)    {
    currentChunk = chunks.next()
  }
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (currentChunk != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; currentChunk.hasRemaining) {
    val amountToGet = math.min(currentChunk.remaining(), length)
    currentChunk.get(dest, offset, amountToGet)
    amountToGet
  } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
    close()
    -1
  }
}&#160;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
